text: The Gajapati dynasty, also called the Suryavamsa dynasty () or the Routray dynasty, was a medieval Hindu dynasty in the Indian subcontinent, originally from the region of Central East India. At its peak, it ruled over an empire stretching from the Ganges in the north near West Bengal to the Kaveri in the south, comprising large parts of Andhra Pradesh and western regions of West Bengal. ==Notes== == References == Category:Pages created with the Article Wizard from 2024 Category:Dynasties in India
title: Gajapati Dynasty
